HEADWORD: dibutyl
<hw>di*bu"tyl</hw> <pr>(d⟦isl⟧*b⟦umac⟧"t⟦icr⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Pref. <ets>di-</ets> + <ets>butyl</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A liquid hydrocarbon, <chform>C8H18</chform>, of the alkane series,
being one of several octanes, and consisting of two butyl radicals. Cf.
<er>Octane</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

